Stock News






Liberty Sirius XM Group (LSXMK) Analysts See $0.38 EPS; Domtar (UFS) Has 1.05 Sentiment


					
						July 28, 2017 - By Vivian Park


Domtar Corporation designs, manufactures, markets and distributes a range of fiber products, including communication papers, specialty and packaging papers and absorbent hygiene products. The company has market cap of $2.40 billion. The Firm divisions include Pulp and Paper and Personal Care. It has a 16.68 P/E ratio. The Pulp and Paper segment consists of the design, manufacturing, marketing and distribution of communication, specialty and packaging papers, as well as softwood, fluff and hardwood market pulp.







 Analysts expect Liberty Sirius XM Group (NASDAQ:LSXMK) to report $0.38 EPS on August, 9 before the open.They anticipate $0.14 EPS change or 58.33% from last quarter’s $0.24 EPS. LSXMK’s profit would be $198.69 million giving it 29.78 P/E if the $0.38 EPS is correct. After having $0.37 EPS previously, Liberty Sirius XM Group’s analysts see 2.70% EPS growth. About 119,458 shares traded. Liberty Sirius XM Group (NASDAQ:LSXMK) has 0.00% since July 28, 2016 and is . It has underperformed by 16.70% the S&P500.
Liberty Media Corporation owns interests in subsidiaries and other companies, which are engaged in the media and entertainment industries. The company has market cap of $23.67 billion. The Company’s principal businesses and assets include its consolidated subsidiaries Sirius XM Holdings Inc. and Braves Holdings, LLC (Braves Holdings), and its equity affiliate Live Nation Entertainment, Inc. (Live Nation). It has a 36.48 P/E ratio. The Company’s divisions are SIRIUS XM, and Corporate and other.
 About 183,551 shares traded. Domtar Corp (USA) (UFS) has declined 0.68% since July 28, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 17.38% the S&P500.
Rock Point Advisors Llc holds 4.18% of its portfolio in Domtar Corp (USA) for 208,217 shares. Fairpointe Capital Llc owns 2.83 million shares or 2.23% of their US portfolio. Moreover, Lombardia Capital Partners Llc has 1.71% invested in the company for 426,801 shares. The New York-based Arbiter Partners Capital Management Llc has invested 1.3% in the stock. Boyer & Corporon Wealth Management Llc, a Kansas-based fund reported 67,693 shares.








By Vivian Park
Echostar Corporation-Receive News & Ratings Via Email - Enter your email address below to receive a concise daily summary of the latest news and analysts' ratings with our FREE daily email newsletter.








 

 




 
