"Product Hunt Radio" to Premiere Exclusively on SiriusXM


May 14, 2015

Download this Press Release (PDF 46 KB)

Product Hunt's Ryan Hoover and Erik Torenberg connect 
the nation with a community of entrepreneurs, investors, and consumers 
to discover the next great apps, software services and tech products


NEW YORK, May 14, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- SiriusXM today announced it will premiere "Product Hunt Radio," an all-new tech-discovery show hosted by Ryan Hoover and Erik Torenberg of Product Hunt,
 the online community where enthusiasts geek out about the latest tech 
products.  "Product Hunt Radio" will showcase what's new in tech, 
provide insight into the people behind the products, and connect with 
the community that has made Product Hunt such a success. 

Each week, Ryan and Erik will invite well-known guests from inside 
the tech scene, including the creators and investors behind many of 
today's most popular tech products, mobile apps, and services, to 
discuss the tech industry in a way that will be informative to tech 
insiders while still accessible to mainstream, product-loving listeners.
  
"The Product Hunt community is about celebrating new products and the
 makers behind them.  'Product Hunt Radio' is an extension of this 
mission, surfacing awesome new products, trends in technology, and 
conversation with the makers," said Ryan Hoover.  "Our 
goal is to provide a platform for makers to tell their stories and have 
an intelligent conversation about innovative, unique products that 
change the way we live."
"Product Hunt has become the destination for in-the-know 
entrepreneurs, investors, and consumers to discover and rate what could 
be the next great thing in tech," said Scott Greenstein,
 President and Chief Content Officer, SiriusXM.  "SiriusXM has been in 
the forefront of broadcasting tech news and information for an audience 
of radio listeners across the country.  Now, with 'Product Hunt Radio,' 
and guidance from Ryan and Erik, listeners will hear first-hand what is 
hot in tech and why."
Gary Vaynerchuk, wine expert, social media 
commentator and best-selling author, will be the first guest of the 
inaugural episode of "Product Hunt Radio."  Future guests will feature a
 diverse slate of successful entrepreneurs and venture investors, 
including Chris Sacca and Matt Mazzeo of Lowercase Capital; Mark Suster of Upfront Ventures; rapper, Nas; Carmelo Anthony of the New York Knicks; and Aaron Levie, Chief Executive Officer, Co-founder & Chairman of Box.
The 6-week series, "Product Hunt Radio," will launch on Saturday, May 16, at 6:00 pm ET, and rebroadcast on Sunday, May 17, at 9:00 pm ET,
 on SiriusXM Insight channel 121, and through the SiriusXM App on 
smartphones and other connected devices, as well as online at siriusxm.com. 
 "Product Hunt Radio" will also be available on SiriusXM On Demand for 
subscribers listening via smartphones and other connected devices or 
online at siriusxm.com. 
Additionally, Hoover and Torenberg will make the show available at www.producthunt.com/radio after its premier on SiriusXM.
Ryan Hoover, 28, is the Founder and CEO of Product 
Hunt, backed by Y Combinator and Andreessen Horowitz.  Hoover is also a 
contributing writer to "Hooked: How to Build Habit-Forming Products" by Nir Eyal and active writer on technology and products with articles featured in Fast Company, TechCrunch, and The Next Web.
Erik Torenberg, 25, is a founding team member at 
Product Hunt. Torenberg previously founded rapt.fm, and he has also been
 an associate at Nas and Anthony Saleh's venture firm, Queensbridge Venture Partners. 
 He is interested in education, media, startups, venture capital, 
accelerators, retreat-models of learning, curriculum design, moderating 
panels, curating conversations, hosting cyphers/book clubs/potlucks, and
 meeting great people.
SiriusXM Insight broadcasts news, information, and entertainment 
offering listeners inspiring ideas and intelligent conversation with an 
edge.  Designed to reach fans that enjoy the eclectic subject matter of 
public radio, SiriusXM Insight features an array of fresh, diverse 
voices addressing a new era of issues in a lively, smart, and sometimes 
humorous approach, including shows hosted by Pete Dominick, John Fugelsang, Dean Obeidallah, Neil deGrasse Tyson, Karen Hunter, Margaret Hoover and more. 
For more information and to try SiriusXM for 30 days, please visit siriusxm.com.
About SiriusXM
Sirius XM Holdings Inc.
 (NASDAQ: SIRI) is the world's largest radio broadcaster measured by 
revenue and has more than 27.7 million subscribers.  SiriusXM creates 
and broadcasts commercial-free music; premier sports talk and live 
events; comedy; news; exclusive talk and entertainment; and the most 
comprehensive Latin music, sports and talk programming in radio. 
SiriusXM is available in vehicles from every major car company in the 
U.S. and on smartphones and other connected devices as well as online at
 siriusxm.com. SiriusXM radios and accessories are available from retailers nationwide and at shop.siriusxm.com. 
 
SiriusXM also provides premium traffic, weather, data and information 
services for subscribers in cars, trucks, RVs, boats and aircraft 
through SiriusXM Traffic™, SiriusXM Travel Link, NavTraffic®, 
NavWeather™, SiriusXM Aviation, SiriusXM Marine™, Sirius Marine Weather, XMWX Aviation™, and XMWX Marine™.  SiriusXM holds a minority interest in SiriusXM Canada
 which has more than 2 million subscribers. SiriusXM is also a leading 
provider of connected vehicles services to major automakers, giving 
customers access to a suite of safety, security, and convenience 
services including automatic crash notification, stolen vehicle recovery
 assistance, enhanced roadside assistance and turn-by-turn navigation.
On social media, join the SiriusXM community on Facebook, Twitter, Instagram, and YouTube.
